Simulation Report
SIMULATION REPORT Pipeline Processor Design using Verilog HDL

Objective

To design and simulate a simple pipeline processor capable of demonstrating instruction flow through multiple pipeline stages using Verilog HDL.

Software Used

Xilinx Vivado Verilog HDL

Pipeline Stages Implemented

Instruction Fetch (IF) Instruction Decode (ID) Execute (EX) Memory Access (MEM) Write Back (WB)

Simulation Procedure

The pipeline processor module was designed using Verilog HDL. A separate testbench was created to generate clock and reset signals. Behavioral simulation was run in Xilinx Vivado. Waveforms were observed to verify correct movement of data through different pipeline stages.

========================================================================================================================================================= Waveform Analysis

The waveform shows the operation of the pipeline processor during different clock cycles. Initially, the reset signal is high, which clears all pipeline registers.

After the reset signal becomes low, data starts moving through different pipeline stages.

At each positive edge of the clock:

IF_ID stores fetched instruction data. ID_EX receives data from IF_ID. EX_MEM receives data from ID_EX. MEM_WB receives data from EX_MEM.

This verifies the correct sequential movement of data through the processor pipeline.

The waveform correctly demonstrates pipelined processor operation and synchronous stage execution.

